    <item>
      <title>电动汽车关税迫在眉睫，欧盟与中国之间仍存在巨大差距</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/significant-gaps-remain-between-eu-and-china-as-ev-tariffs-loom</link>
      <description><![CDATA[欧盟在一份声明中表示，在为避免本月底对中国产电动汽车征收关税而进行的八轮谈判之后，欧盟与北京方面仍然存在“重大分歧”。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/significant-gaps-remain-between-eu-and-china-as-ev-tariffs-loom</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2024 06:12:01 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>印尼加入越来越多渴望加入金砖国家的国家行列</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/indonesia-joins-growing-list-of-nations-keen-to-be-part-of-brics</link>
      <description><![CDATA[印尼已启动加入金砖国家的进程，这表明金砖国家的影响力日益增强，并将自己定位为美国主导的全球秩序的替代者。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/indonesia-joins-growing-list-of-nations-keen-to-be-part-of-brics</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2024 05:43:04 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>德国欧洲文化之都回顾动荡历史</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2024-10-25/germany-s-chemnitz-european-capital-of-culture-2025-has-some-grand-plans</link>
      <description><![CDATA[开姆尼茨一直是德国经济和政治问题的先锋。作为 2025 年欧洲文化之都，它希望成为解决方案的一部分。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2024-10-25/germany-s-chemnitz-european-capital-of-culture-2025-has-some-grand-plans</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2024 04:00:24 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>瑞士人喜欢欧盟的经济利益，而不是欧盟本身</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/swiss-like-the-eu-s-economic-benefits-not-so-much-the-eu-itself</link>
      <description><![CDATA[一项新民意调查显示，瑞士努力与欧盟建立更紧密联系，但这一努力将很难得到选民的支持，因为约有一半的选民对欧盟持怀疑态度。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/swiss-like-the-eu-s-economic-benefits-not-so-much-the-eu-itself</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>英国新反骚扰法或将终结醉酒工作派对</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/boozy-work-parties-may-be-over-with-new-uk-harassment-law</link>
      <description><![CDATA[英国雇主正在考虑制定新规，要求公司保护员工免受性骚扰，否则将面临巨额索赔的风险，因此以酒精为主要燃料的公司活动可能会成为过去。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/boozy-work-parties-may-be-over-with-new-uk-harassment-law</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>俄罗斯将把关键利率恢复至入侵后的水平</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/russia-set-to-return-key-rate-to-level-seen-in-wake-of-invasion</link>
      <description><![CDATA[由于政策制定者难以控制物价快速上涨，俄罗斯央行准备在周五将其基准利率上调至总统弗拉基米尔·普京下令入侵乌克兰后设定的创纪录水平。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/russia-set-to-return-key-rate-to-level-seen-in-wake-of-invasion</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>无论谁赢得大选，韩国都将继续投资美国</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/south-korea-vows-to-keep-investing-in-us-whoever-wins-election</link>
      <description><![CDATA[韩国财政部长崔相默表示，无论下个月选举结果如何，韩国都希望与美国保持密切关系，并将在华盛顿和北京持续的竞争中寻找机会。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-25/south-korea-vows-to-keep-investing-in-us-whoever-wins-election</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Oct 2024 01:07:31 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>莫桑比克执政党赢得选举 选举舞弊指控</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-24/mozambique-s-ruling-party-wins-vote-tainted-by-fraud-allegations</link>
      <description><![CDATA[莫桑比克执政党候选人被宣布为总统选举的绝对赢家，但因欺诈指控而产生的紧张局势使这个东南部非洲国家陷入紧张局势，并导致其债券暴跌。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-24/mozambique-s-ruling-party-wins-vote-tainted-by-fraud-allegations</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 24 Oct 2024 14:27:17 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>里夫斯确认英国将实施新财政规则 以应对投资者税收担忧</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-24/reeves-says-uk-fiscal-rule-change-will-increase-investment</link>
      <description><![CDATA[英国财政大臣雷切尔·里夫斯 (Rachel Reeves) 赞同一项财政改革，该改革可能使英国在未来五年内可以再借入高达 700 亿英镑（910 亿美元）的资金，同时英国政府为一项似乎越来越有可能向投资者征税的预算进行辩护。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-24/reeves-says-uk-fiscal-rule-change-will-increase-investment</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 24 Oct 2024 13:39:16 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
